divs: sighting detailswhile waiting to observe international space station (iss)and shuttle atlantis during the evening of may 14th, observed a dark, point like object at a great distance to the west-northwest. object was at altitude higher than cloud deck. object did not leave visible contrails. object appeared to move much more slowly than observed commercial aircraft. object did not reflect sunlight as did observed commercial aircraft. first sighted at approx 30 deg above horizon, appeared to move due west, poss. south west at slow rate of speed. object slowly faded from view approx 27 deg above horizon due to distance\ altitude.
Summary: Dark, slow moving, high altitude object observed near sunset
